# ebi_decode -- WO-56 deliverable 6: `by select(...)`, the sixth impl
# strategy (D161), over three real external-bus-interface (EBI)
# address-decode alternatives for a memory-mapped peripheral: discrete
# 74HC-series NOR/AND glue logic, a CPLD, or an MCU with its own
# built-in FSMC/EBI chip-select controller (the std.civil... no --
# `ti.logic`/`microchip.cpld`/`st.mcu` WO-60/D166 stdlib records this
# demo's candidates are named after). `regolith.orchestrator.optimize`'s
# `optimize_discrete` (Python) reads this board's real, lowered
# `BuildPayload.choice_points` entry and picks the policy-best
# candidate under a declared cost objective; flipping the declared
# cost order flips the winner (the WO-56 policy-flip test,
# `tests/test_wo56_ebi_decode.py`).
#
# The choice point itself is the only thing this file needs to prove
# end to end -- `select`'s candidate refs are diagnostics-only labels
# at this L1/L2 tier (checks.rs's own `check_select_candidates` never
# resolves them; see contracts.rs's `select_choice_point`), so no
# `nor_glue`/`cpld`/`mcu_chip_selects` declaration is required here.

board decoder_board:
    impl AddressDecodeGlue by select(nor_glue, cpld, mcu_chip_selects)

    # WO-105 release residuals (D206/D207): memo-backed accepted
    # deviations; verdicts untouched (INV-2). See memos/release-residuals.md.
    waive impl(AddressDecodeGlue):
        basis: "interface conformance edge: `by select(...)` candidate list unresolved at release, no scalar window on a bare impl binding (D195.3); addressable per D215"
        by doc(memos/release-residuals.md)
